1. Aligns with National PE Standards (SHAPE America)

Most districts follow SHAPE America.

Your program directly supports all 5 core standards:

✅ Standard 1 — Motor Skills & Movement
Strength training (squat, clean, bench)
Movement/stability work
Timed rotations

👉 Students demonstrate competency in movement patterns

✅ Standard 2 — Understanding Concepts
Percent-based lifting (like your “65%” display)
Reps, sets, progression
Training structure (core lift / aux lift / movement)

👉 Students learn why they train, not just what

✅ Standard 3 — Physical Activity & Fitness
Daily structured workouts
Measurable performance outputs (vert, broad, agility, etc.)

👉 Meets moderate-to-vigorous activity requirements

✅ Standard 4 — Personal & Social Behavior
Rotations + stations
Shared equipment
Accountability through tracking

👉 Builds teamwork + responsibility

✅ Standard 5 — Values Physical Activity
Leaderboards
Progress tracking
Visible improvement over time

👉 Encourages long-term engagement in fitness
